# Optional: shared jobs for the whole team (Supabase Postgres).
# 1. Create a project at https://supabase.com
# 2. Run SQL from supabase/jobs_list.sql and supabase/driver_positions.sql in the SQL Editor.
#    If driver_positions already existed without job_ids, also run supabase/driver_positions_job_ids.sql.
# 3. Copy Project URL and anon public key from Project Settings → API Keys
#
# Copy this file to `.env` and fill in real values (never commit `.env`).

VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-ref.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-public-key

# If unset, jobs stay in browser localStorage only (per device).

# Optional: Google Maps JavaScript API key (Places) for address lookup on job create / edit.
# Enable "Maps JavaScript API" and "Places API" in Google Cloud; restrict the key by HTTP referrer.
# VITE_GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY=

# Optional: Microsoft Entra app (SPA) for Settings → OneDrive PDF backup upload.
# Azure Portal → App registrations → New → Single-page application.
# Authentication → Add platform → SPA → Redirect URI: https://your-domain/onedrive-callback (and http://localhost:5173/onedrive-callback for dev).
# API permissions → Microsoft Graph → Delegated: Files.ReadWrite, openid, profile, offline_access.
# Expose only the public Application (client) ID here:
# VITE_MS_CLIENT_ID=your-azure-client-id
